All three lemmas hold on every DB model.

Open proof structure:
  L1 is algebraically provable from E677 + left-cancel.
  L2 follows from L1 + squaring identity + left-cancel.
  L3 is the main open step: E677 + finite => R_x injective on O_x.

Key gap in L3 (cascade argument):
  d_i = d_j (collision) implies R_{d_i} acts on (c_{i-1}, c_{j-1})
  by the L1 recurrence.  The cascade needs d_{i-1} = d_{j-1} ALSO
  to continue — this is the unproved step.  L2b pins d_{d-2} = x,
  giving a known 'anchor' in the d-sequence that the cascade must hit.

To attack L3:
  1. Try to build an E677 model (via DPLL / model search in src/) where
     E255 fails.  If impossible for all n, it suggests E677 => E255.
  2. Try to prove the cascade directly: show d_i = d_j and L2b together
     force i = j (mod d) without needing all intermediate d_{i-k} = d_{j-k}.
  3. Use the ATP files in atp/ to check if E677 + left-cancel + (d_i = d_j)
     + L2b gives a contradiction in first-order logic.

